The seat fell vacant following the death of Senator Boniface Kabaka (Chama Cha Uzalendo) late last year.
IEBC had also set February 18 for the Nairobi gubernatorial by-election following the impeachment of former governor Mike Sonko but the High Court on Monday suspended a Gazette notice calling for the vote.
In his ruling, Justice Anthony Mrima temporarily stopped the mini poll on the basis of Sonko’s petition challenging the process that led to his ouster late last year.





Other by-elections
Other planned by-elections to be conducted by IEBC on March 4, 2021 and whose timelines have not been affected include those for Matungu and Kabuchai constituencies and five for members of county assemblies for Hell’s Gate and London wards in Nakuru County, Huruma, Kiamokama and Kitise/Kithuku wards in Uasin Gishu, Kisii and Makueni counties respectively.
“The timelines in part, as contained in the Gazette notices in the schedule herein and pursuant to Section 31 (2b) and (2c) of the Elections Act number 24 of 2011 provide that a political party submits to the commission names of persons contesting in its party primaries before the nomination day and that the commission shall publish the said names in the Gazette,” Mr Chebukati said.



