He disclosed that the commission had equally shared the list with the government printer for publication.
“Further, Section 32 and 33 provide that persons intending to contest as independent candidates shall submit to the commission symbols they intend to use in an election.
“The commission in turn is required to publish in the Kenya Gazette, the names and symbols of the persons.”
The IEBC Chairman noted that the names and symbols of the aspirants had also been forwarded to the government printer for publication.
He reiterated that the publication of names of persons contesting in party primaries and those intending to contest as independent candidates is not “clearance of candidates to contest in an election”.
“Clearance of candidates for purposes of contesting in an election is done during the days set for nomination by the respective returning officers that have been duly appointed by the commission,” said Mr Chebukati. For Uhuru, Raila, Ruto, Kalonzo, Mudavadi and Wetang’ula, outcome of mini polls a pointer to referendum, 2022 The mini-poll will find a successor for MP Justus Murunga who died last month. Senate Majority Chief Whip says he did not give the letter to any media outlet. The hospitals in Nyamira, Homa Bay and Migori counties that were involved in various forms of fraud. Some learners forced to study under trees as most learning institutions face the social distancing nightmare.